By: \'Abd al-Razzâq al-Qashânî
---
Insofar as man is a possibility of manifestation, but does not see What
manifests him, he is pure absence ('udum); by contrast, insofar as he receives
his being from the perpetual irradiation (Tajalli) of the Essence, he is.
